The error is that `is_micro_company` takes `(Company, FinancialYear)` but the rules phase couldn't ground `fy` in the consequent. The fix is to remove `FinancialYear` from `is_micro_company`'s signature and instead make the helper/observable predicates about the company's last closed financial year implicitly (i.e., make the criterion-exceeded predicates unary on `Company`, referring to the last closed financial year by definition). This way `is_micro_company(Company)` has no ungrounded variable.

